## Hugging Face MCP Server

### Model/Dataset Discovery
- `model_search` — params: `query`, `sort` (`trendingScore`|`downloads`|`likes`), `limit` (max 100), `author`, `library`, `task`
- `dataset_search` — params: `query`, `sort`, `limit` (max 100), `author`, `tags`
- `hub_repo_details` — params: `repo_ids` (max 10, format `author/name`), `repo_type`

### Research & Documentation
- `paper_search` — params: `query` (3-200 chars), `results_limit`, `concise_only` (use `true` for broad searches)
- `hf_doc_search` — params: `query`, `product`; start with empty query for structure
- `hf_doc_fetch` — params: `doc_url`, `offset` (for large docs)

### Other
- `space_search` — params: `query`, `limit`, `mcp` (filter MCP-enabled)
- `gr1_flux1_schnell_infer` — image generation; params: `prompt` (max 60-70 words), `width`/`height` (256-2048), `num_inference_steps` (1-16, default 4)
- `hf_whoami` — auth status (currently: `microgrampictures`)

### Workflow
1. Use filters (`author`, `task`, `library`) to narrow search
2. After finding models → `hub_repo_details` for specs
3. Papers: `concise_only: true` for broad topics → full abstracts for specific
4. Docs: `hf_doc_search` → `hf_doc_fetch`

### Troubleshooting
- Auth errors: verify HF token with `hf_whoami`
- Repo not found: check exact `author/name` format
- If `repo_type` auto-detect fails, specify explicitly
